article.headline: Texas St. 66, Texas-San Antonio 52
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- -- Matt Staff scored 28 points and grabbed 12 rebounds on Saturday to spark Texas State past the University of Texas San Antonio 66-52. Staff also had six assists for Texas State (13-15, 5-9 Southland). He scored 17 points in the second half as Texas State pulled away after trailing 27-26 at the break. Brooks Ybarra scored 14 points for Texas State. Jeromie Hill scored 14 points to lead UTSA (16-13, 8-6) and Stephen Franklin had 10 points and three steals. Texas State had a 20-18 scoring advantage in the paint and 15-6 off turnovers, but its bench was outscored 20-4.
